&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help empower our global customers to connect to culture through their passions.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why you’ll love this role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;StockX is seeking an experienced and detail-oriented Senior Manager of International Indirect Tax to join our&amp;nbsp;Global Tax team. This is a high-visibility role with direct engagement with senior finance leadership and meaningful&amp;nbsp;exposure to international tax planning and strategic business initiatives. In this role you will own the end-to-end&amp;nbsp;international indirect tax compliance function spanning VAT, GST, IOSS, OSS and Intrastat obligations across all&amp;nbsp;StockX’s operational jurisdictions outside the United States. A core responsibility of this position is to ensure the&amp;nbsp;tax efficiency of new international business initiatives while proactively identifying and limiting potential indirect&amp;nbsp;tax exposure to both the Company and its customers. You will serve as a trusted advisor and subject matter expert&amp;nbsp;across Finance, Accounting, Legal, Product, and Business Operations translating complex, rapidly evolving cross-border tax obligations into clear guidance and scalable compliance frameworks that support StockX’s continued&amp;nbsp;global growth&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform monthly and quarterly review of all non-U.S. indirect tax adjustments, including IOSS and OSS&lt;br&gt;compliance filings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead monthly review of Intrastat filings across applicable EU member states.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review proposed monthly indirect tax journal entries and manage ERP approval of corresponding&lt;br&gt;postings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze month-over-month balance sheet flux for each indirect tax account and provide a high-level&lt;br&gt;comprehensive explanation of the identified variances.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare monthly indirect tax movement KPI reports for VP review and presentation to Finance leaders&lt;br&gt;during the month’s CFO review meeting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage monthly and quarterly preparation of indirect tax reserves in accordance with applicable&lt;br&gt;accounting standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the annual financial statement process, including reconciliations, journal entries, and support&lt;br&gt;schedules.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and support indirect tax audits, notices, IDRs, and controversy matters, including gathering&lt;br&gt;documentation, performing reconciliations and analysis, coordinating responses, and maintaining audit&lt;br&gt;trackers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain recordkeeping for indirect tax filings, indirect tax notices and audit documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor indirect tax legislation changes relevant to StockX, research the impact, and help drive&lt;br&gt;implementation of necessary changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate the indirect tax implications of new international business initiatives, lead or support cross-&lt;br&gt;functional implementation of process enhancements in partnership with Finance, Legal, Product, and&lt;br&gt;Operations departments, and develop scalable, audit-ready compliance frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with registrations, annual compliance requirements, special projects, and ad hoc requests from&lt;br&gt;business partners and external advisors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach, mentor, and develop tax professionals at all levels by providing regular feedback, supporting career growth, building succession plans, and fostering a culture of accountability, collaboration, and continuous learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in international indirect tax, including VAT/GST/JCT compliance and adviso

